{
  "texts": [
    "Note that the approaches described in the following sections also use word embeddings.",
    "The starting point is a tokenised text, obtained from a pre-processing process as explained in Section 3.1.1.",
    "The word embedding is applied to these tokens.",
    "In practical applications, the volume of available text data may not be sufficiently large to train embeddings from scratch.",
    "In this case, pre-trained embeddings can be used, which are available in packages such as Pennington et al. (2014) and Bird et al. (2009), trained on Wikipedia and other large text corpuses."
  ]
}